-- Yen Gains Versus Euro, Dollar on Asian Stock Drop, Signs Recovery Sluggish
-- B y   R o n n i e   H a r u i
-- 2010-10-29T01:02:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/dollar-drops-against-euro-on-speculation-fed-easing-will-debase-currency.html
The yen strengthened as a drop in
Asian stocks and signs the global recovery is sluggish boosted
demand for Japan’s currency as a refuge.  The yen climbed to 112.45 per euro as of 10:01 a.m. in
Tokyo from 112.87 in New York yesterday. Japan’s currency was at
80.88 per dollar from 81.03.  To contact the reporter on this story:
